FBIS3-25486 "drafr035_c_94011" FBIS-AFR-94-035 Document Type:Daily Report 22 Feb 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Minister Meyer: Sovereign Zulu State `Impossible' MB2002173094 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 1600 GMT 20 Feb 94 MB2002173094 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The minister of constitutional affairs, Mr. Roelf Meyer, says it will be impossible for [Zulu] King Zwelithini to have a sovereign state. Speaking at Noordgezicht near Johannesburg, Mr. Meyer said, however, that there was nothing against the king having control over his subjects. He said he saw the best solution as writing the king's sovereignty into a provincial constitution.
